message: I have been following the farmers agitation for a long time now . It was very confusing initially .  But now it's disgusting .   I read somewhere that promise of the new changes in farm laws were in the Congress manifesto of 2019 ,   I saw mr Pawar's interview as Central agriculture minister in which he proposed the same changes that are in the new law.   I saw an  interview of Mr Kejriwal where he proposed that the same changes be made in the farm laws.   And now these guys are opposing the same.   Then the  government had a series of meetings with the farmers' leaders which were inconclusive.  Then  the supreme court suggested that an expert  committee be formed to go through the clauses with a fine tooth comb and get both parties to come to an agreement, which the farmers rejected. Then the government agreed that the laws will be kept in abeyance for the next 18 months till an amicable solution is found, which the farmers rejected.  And today they invade Delhi city , break all the laws ,  destroy public and private property ,  attack with swords , beat up on duty police personnel.  And now I feel enough is enough.
